# StrAppers frontend — canonical paths

The **student-facing React app** lives under **`strAppersFrontend/src/`** (not the repo root).

| Area | Path |
|------|------|
| Pages (e.g. student projects UI) | `strAppersFrontend/src/pages/` — includes `ProjectsStudentV2.jsx`, `CategoryProjects.jsx` |
| HTTP wrappers to .NET backend | `strAppersFrontend/src/api/*StrAppers.js` |
| Shared components | `strAppersFrontend/src/components/` |
| Legacy/Base44 function sources (Deno) | `strAppersFrontend/base44/functions/` |

When the user mentions **ProjectsStudentV2**, **get-students**, **invokeGetProjectStudents**, or **student project browsing**, search **`strAppersFrontend/src`** first. Do not assume `strAppersFrontend` only contains a landing page.

Indexer note: `strAppersFrontend/node_modules` and build folders are excluded via root **`.cursorignore`** so tools can enumerate `src` reliably.

## “As you go” path indexing

If the user **states a concrete path** to a page, component, API module, or folder (e.g. “X is in `…/src/pages/…`”), **in the same change**:

1. **Append** a row to **`docs/FRONTEND_PATH_INDEX.md`** (Path + one-line Context). Avoid duplicates for the same path; update Context if the old note is wrong.
2. Optionally extend the table in this rule’s **canonical paths** section only when it’s a **new top-level area** (e.g. a new major directory).

Future agents should **read `docs/FRONTEND_PATH_INDEX.md`** when working on frontend tasks so known locations accumulate without re-discovery.
